snippet.textDisplay:
There are times when others don't understand you but you still keep on your path.
Why?

The answer is because you understand that you are right.

This Poetry was that time for Iqbal.
When he wrote Shikwam Molanas called him Kafir, they called him jew, they called him non-muslim.
And then he wrote Jawab-e-Shikwa and now that poetry that made others call him Kafir is now taught in Pakistani Schools and is considered one of the best works of Allama Iqbal.

Sometimes it is enough to believe that you are right even when others dont agree with you because you are the only one who knows what you are doing and why......It is enough if only you know it

BTW this was awesome .....the female singer and then the last 1 minute was powerful
